claim.claim-text:
9. A method for selecting the most favorable elevator of a elevator installation having at least two elevator groups, wherein a route with changeovers is available for reaching a destination floor from a start floor, comprising the steps of: 
a. breaking down a route having at least one changeover between a start floor and a destination floor into several stretches; 
b. breaking down at least one further route having at least one changeover between the start floor and the destination floor into several stretches; 
c. comparing operating costs of the stretches of the route and the at least one further route to determine the most favorable route; and 
d. allocating an elevator of one of at least two elevator groups to each of the stretches of the most favorable route.
